# CODEOWNERS — Architecture Guardians
# Any change to these paths requires review from @fconsertt-source
# This enforces architectural boundaries at the PR review level

# Core Domain Layer — Pure business rules (no external dependencies allowed)
/src/domain/          @fconsertt-source

# Application Layer — Pure Use Cases + DTOs (no infrastructure dependencies allowed)
/src/application/     @fconsertt-source

# Infrastructure Layer — Adapters only (must implement Application Ports)
/src/infrastructure/  @fconsertt-source

# Presentation Layer — Formatting/Wiring only (no business logic allowed)
/src/presentation/    @fconsertt-source

# Architectural Decision Records — Changes require architecture review
/docs/adr/            @fconsertt-source

# Guard Scripts — Critical for architectural enforcement
/scripts/check_*.py   @fconsertt-source
